### CSS At-Rules

**At-rules** are CSS statements starting with `@` that control behavior.

---

### Common At-Rules

| At-Rule | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `@media` | Apply styles based on media conditions |
| `@keyframes` | Define animation steps |
| `@font-face` | Load custom fonts |
| `@import` | Import another stylesheet |
| `@supports` | Apply styles based on browser support |
| `@layer` | Organize CSS into layers |
| `@container` | Apply styles based on container size |
| `@scope` | Limit styles to a subtree |
| `@starting-style` | Styles for first-time rendering |
| `@property` | Define custom properties with types |

---

### @media

```css
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container { max-width: 720px; }
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  body { background: #111; color: #eee; }
}
```

---

### @keyframes

```css
@keyframes slideIn {
  from { transform: translateX(-100%); }
  to { transform: translateX(0); }
}
```

---

### @font-face

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'CustomFont';
  src: url('font.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-display: swap;
}
```

---

### @import

```css
@import url('reset.css');
@import url('theme.css') screen and (min-width: 768px);
```

---

### @supports

```css
@supports (display: grid) {
  .container { display: grid; }
}

@supports not (display: grid) {
  .container { display: flex; }
}
```

---

### @layer

```css
@layer base, components, utilities;

@layer base {
  body { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
}

@layer components {
  .card { padding: 20px; }
}

@layer utilities {
  .m-0 { margin: 0; }
}
```

---

### Nesting @rules

```css
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  @layer content {
    .card {
      display: grid;
      gap: 20px;
    }
  }
}
```

> **Key Point:** Only `@import` must be at the top of the file. All other at-rules can be placed anywhere.
